description:
&lt;p&gt;STAFF COUNSELLOR&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;BAND 7 £40,894 - £44,503 (pro rata)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Inclusive of high cost area allowance&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;3days per week (22.5hrs)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1yr fixed term contract&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Opportunity to join CONTACT – the Staff Counselling, Stress Management, Conflict Resolution and Trauma Service for Imperial College Healthcare Trust, based at 3 major hospital sites: Charing Cross, Hammersmith and St. Mary’s. CONTACT is a comprehensive support service for staff at all levels of the Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be a BACP/UKCP/BPS accredited practitioner with substantial experience of a wide range of clients and time-limited work. You will have knowledge and experience of work-place counselling, related research and the challenges and ethical dilemmas presented in this area of work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition you must have group facilitation, training and supervisory experience and therapeutic skills to a senior practitioner level. You will be able to work with groups of staff dealing with conflict. And able to support individual and groups of staff experiencing traumatic incidences. Integrated and transcultural approach essential in all areas of work. You will be required to work across the hospital sites.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer a flexible approach to working hours to meet the needs of the individual and the service. Please talk to us at interview about the flexibility you may need.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like an informal discussion about the post phone the CONTACT team on 020 331 32747/21519&lt;/p&gt;
